Reasoning: The paper introduces a generalized framework for compressed sensing of analog signals, which is likely to fall under the Information Theory (cs.IT) and Signal Processing (cs.SP) categories. The paper also discusses applications in multiband communications, finite rate of innovation signals, and sparse harmonic tones, which are relevant to the Multidimensional Signal Processing (cs.MM) and Sampling Theory (cs.SI) categories. Finally, the paper emphasizes a hardware-oriented viewpoint, which could also make it relevant to the Embedded Systems (cs.EM) category.
